String:
    It is collection of characters or sequence of characters

STRING manipulation Techniques:
    1.length
    2.reverse
    3.Compare
    4.range/index
    5.map
    6.toupper
    7.tolower
    8.first
    9.last
    10.trimleft
    11.trimright
Syntax:
       set variable name
       set variable "name1 name2 name3"
       set variable {name1 name2 name3}
Example:
      set PD_TOPICS PnR
      set PD "Floorplan Powerplan Placement"
      set pd_topics {CTS Routing signoff}
      puts $PD_TOPICS
      puts $PD
      puts $pd_topics

1. string length:
    it is used to find the length of the string inclusing spaces.
syntax:
      string length $variable_name
Example 1:
      set a "this is tcl class"
      set b [string length $a]
      puts $b
Example 2:
      set str "Hello, world!"
      set length [string length $str]
      puts "Length of the string: $length"

2. string reverse
   it is used to reverse the string
syntax: 
    string reverse $variable_name
Example 1:
      set a "this is tcl class"
      set b [string reverse $a]
      puts $b
Example 2:
      set str "abcde"
      set reversed_str [string reverse $str]
      puts "Reversed string: $reversed_str"

3. string compare:
    Compares two strings lexicographically and returns -1 if the first string is less than the second, 0 if they are equal, and 1 if the first string is greater than the second.
Syntax:
    string compare $variable1 $varibale2

Examples:
# String compare if string1 and string2 is same, prints output is 0
      set a "this is tcl class"
      set b "this is tcl class"
      set c [string compare $a $b]
      puts "its prints output is:$c"

# String compare if string1 lessthan and string2 , prints output is -1
      set a "this is tcl cla"
      set b "this is tcl class"
      set c [string compare $a $b]
      puts "its prints output is:$c"

# String compare if string1 greater than and string2 , prints output is 1
      set a "this is tcl classs"
      set b "this is tcl class"
      set c [string compare $a $b]
      puts "its prints output is:$c"

Example 2:
      set str1 "hello"
      set str2 "world"
      set comparison_result [string compare $str1 $str2]
      if {$comparison_result == 0} {
       puts "Strings are equal"
      } else {
       puts "Strings are not equal"
      }
4. string index:
syntax:
    string index $variable_name index
Examples:
    set s1 "Physical Design"
    set s2 "D"
    puts "First occurrence of $s2 in s1"
    puts [string first $s2 $s1]
    puts "Character at index 0 in s1"
    puts [string index $s1 0]
    puts "Last occurrence of $s2 in s1"
    puts [string last $s2 $s1]
    puts "Word end index in s1"
    puts [string wordend $s1 20]
    puts "Word start index in s1"
    puts [string wordstart $s1 20]
Example 2:
    set str "abcde"
    set char [string index $str 2]
    puts "Character at index 2: $char"

5. string range:
syntax:
    string range $variable_name index1 index 2
Example :
    set str "Hello, world!"
    set substring [string range $str 7 11]
    puts "Substring: $substring"

6. string map:
    set str "abcde"
    set mapped_str [string map {a b} {1 2} $str]
    puts "Mapped string: $mapped_str" # Output: 12cde

7. string append:
    set str "Hello"
    string append str " world!"
    puts "Appended string: $str" # Output: Hello world!

8. string tolower:
    set str "Hello, World!"
    set lowercase_str [string tolower $str]
    puts "Lowercase string: $lowercase_str" # Output: hello, world!

9. string toupper:
    set str "Hello, World!"
    set uppercase_str [string toupper $str]
    puts "Uppercase string: $uppercase_str" # Output: HELLO, WORLD!

10. string trim:
      set str " Hello, world! "
      set trimmed_str [string trim $str]
      puts "Trimmed string: $trimmed_str" # Output: Hello, world!

11. string trimleft:
      set str " Hello, world!"
      set trimmed_str [string trimleft $str]
      puts "Left-trimmed string: $trimmed_str" # Output: Hello, world!

12. string trimright:
      set str "Hello, world! "
      set trimmed_str [string trimright $str]
      puts "Right-trimmed string: $trimmed_str" # Output: Hello, world!

13. string equal:
      set str1 "hello"
      set str2 "world"
      if {[string equal $str1 $str2]} {
       puts "Strings are equal"
      } else {
       puts "Strings are not equal"
      } # Output: Strings are not equal

14. string is:
      set str "hello"
      if {[string is alpha $str]} {
       puts "String contains only alphabetic characters"
      } # Output: String contains only alphabetic characters

15. string match:
      set str "hello world"
      if {[string match "hello*" $str]} {
       puts "String starts with 'hello'"
      } # Output: String starts with 'hello'

16. string replace:
      set str "Hello, world!"
      set replaced_str [string replace $str 7 11 "there"]
      puts "Replaced string: $replaced_str" # Output: Hello, there!

21. string cat:
      set str1 "Hello"
      set str2 " world!"
      set concatenated_str [string cat $str1 $str2]
      puts "Concatenated string: $concatenated_str" # Output: Hello world!

22. string join:
      set list {"Hello" "world!"}
      set joined_str [string join " " $list]
      puts "Joined string: $joined_str" # Output: Hello world!

23. string format:
      set name "Ajaykumarburada"
      set age 24
      set formatted_str [string format "My name is %s and I am %d years old." $name $age]
      puts "Formatted string: $formatted_str" # Output: My name is Ajaykumarburada and I am 24 years old.
      


